import java.util.Scanner;
class intern {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("Enter the number :");
        int a=sc.nextInt();
        if(a%2==0)
        {
            System.out.println("Even number");
        }
        else{
            System.out.println("Odd number");
        }
    }
}



   Interview questions answers
   1.Modulo operator used in java to find out the remainder of given number.
   2.If and Else statements are used to check the condition whether it is true or false.
   3.Scanner is used to read the input from the user.
   4.We use the nextInt() method to get integer input from the user.
   5.Byte , Short , Int ,Long are all the data types used for numeric values in java.
   6.Yes if condition can hava multiple logical expressions.
   7.Input mismatch Exception is displayed if non negattive number entered.
   8.The remainder will have the same sign of left operand.
   9.Default value of integer in java is "0" value.
   10.Yes can extend an Even/Odd checker to keep running until the user chooses to exit by using a loop like while or do-while and asking the user each time whether to continue.
